#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.162"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.162:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.162:0.2"
msgid "17. Āghātavagga"
msgstr "17. Resentment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.162:0.3"
msgid "162. Dutiyaāghātapaṭivinayasutta"
msgstr "162. Getting Rid of Resentment (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an5.162:1.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an5.162:1.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an5.162:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.187"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcime, āvuso, āghātapaṭivinayā yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso "
"paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, a mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid "
"of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone."

msgctxt "an5.162:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.162:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti parisuddhavacīsamācāro;"
msgstr ""
"In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body is impure, but whose "
"behavior by way of speech is pure,"

msgctxt "an5.162:2.4"
msgid "evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr "you should get rid of resentment for that kind of person."

msgctxt "an5.162:2.5"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti "
"parisuddhakāyasamācāro;"
msgstr ""
"In the case of a person whose behavior by way of speech is impure, but whose "
"behavior by way of body is pure, …"

msgctxt "an5.162:2.6"
msgid "evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.162:2.7"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti "
"aparisuddhavacīsamācāro, labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso "
"pasādaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is impure, "
"but who gets an openness and clarity of heart from time to time, …"

msgctxt "an5.162:2.8"
msgid "evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.162:2.9"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti "
"aparisuddhavacīsamācāro, na ca labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso "
"pasādaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is impure, "
"and who doesn’t get an openness and clarity of heart from time to time, …"

msgctxt "an5.162:2.10"
msgid "evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.162:2.11"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo parisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro, "
"labhati ca kālena vā kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is pure, "
"and who gets an openness and clarity of heart from time to time,"

msgctxt "an5.162:2.12"
msgid "evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr "you should get rid of resentment for that kind of person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro, "
"kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?"
msgstr ""
"How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of "
"body is impure, but whose behavior by way of speech is pure?"

#. VAR: niggaṇhitvā → niggahetvā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: pattharitvā → vitthāretvā (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: paripātetvā → paripāṭetvā (bj) | paripācetvā (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.162:3.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, bhikkhu paṃsukūliko rathiyāya nantakaṃ disvā vāmena "
"pādena niggaṇhitvā dakkhiṇena pādena pattharitvā, yo tattha sāro taṃ "
"paripātetvā ādāya pakkameyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a mendicant wearing rag robes sees a rag by the side of the road. "
"They’d hold it down with the left foot, spread it out with the right foot, "
"tear out what was intact, and take it away with them."

msgctxt "an5.162:3.3"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ khvāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro "
"parisuddhavacīsamācāro, yāssa aparisuddhakāyasamācāratā na sāssa tasmiṃ "
"samaye manasi kātabbā, yā ca khvassa parisuddhavacīsamācāratā sāssa tasmiṃ "
"samaye manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure "
"behavior by way of body and focus on their pure behavior by way of speech."

msgctxt "an5.162:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (1)"
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.188"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhavacīsamācāro parisuddhakāyasamācāro, "
"kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?"
msgstr ""
"How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of "
"speech is impure, but whose behavior by way of body is pure?"

msgctxt "an5.162:4.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, pokkharaṇī sevālapaṇakapariyonaddhā."
msgstr "Suppose there was a lotus pond covered with moss and aquatic plants."

msgctxt "an5.162:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched."

# iticiti ca = iti ca iti ca= “here and there”
msgctxt "an5.162:4.4"
msgid ""
"So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā ubhohi hatthehi iticiti ca sevālapaṇakaṃ "
"apaviyūhitvā añjalinā pivitvā pakkameyya."
msgstr ""
"They’d plunge into the lotus pond, sweep apart the moss and aquatic plants, "
"drink from their cupped hands, and be on their way."

msgctxt "an5.162:4.5"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhavacīsamācāro "
"parisuddhakāyasamācāro, yāssa aparisuddhavacīsamācāratā na sāssa tasmiṃ "
"samaye manasi kātabbā, yā ca khvassa parisuddhakāyasamācāratā sāssa tasmiṃ "
"samaye manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure "
"behavior by way of speech and focus on their pure behavior by way of body."

msgctxt "an5.162:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (2)"
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.189"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro aparisuddhavacīsamācāro "
"labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale "
"āghāto paṭivinetabbo?"
msgstr ""
"How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of "
"body and speech is impure, but who gets an openness and clarity of heart "
"from time to time?"

#. VAR: gopade → gopadake (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.162:5.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, parittaṃ gopade udakaṃ."
msgstr "Suppose there was a little water in a cow’s hoofprint."

msgctxt "an5.162:5.3"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched."

msgctxt "an5.162:5.4"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They might think:"

msgctxt "an5.162:5.5"
msgid "‘idaṃ kho parittaṃ gopade udakaṃ."
msgstr "‘This little bit of water is in a cow’s hoofprint."

msgctxt "an5.162:5.6"
msgid ""
"Sacāhaṃ añjalinā vā pivissāmi bhājanena vā khobhessāmipi taṃ loḷessāmipi taṃ "
"apeyyampi taṃ karissāmi."
msgstr ""
"If I drink it with my cupped hands or a bowl, I’ll stir it and disturb it, "
"making it undrinkable."

msgctxt "an5.162:5.7"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ catukkuṇḍiko nipatitvā gopītakaṃ pivitvā pakkameyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I get down on all fours and drink it up like a cow, then be on my "
"way?’"

msgctxt "an5.162:5.8"
msgid "So catukkuṇḍiko nipatitvā gopītakaṃ pivitvā pakkameyya."
msgstr "So that’s what they do."

msgctxt "an5.162:5.9"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro "
"aparisuddhavacīsamācāro labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso "
"pasādaṃ, yāssa aparisuddhakāyasamācāratā na sāssa tasmiṃ samaye manasi "
"kātabbā;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure "
"behavior by way of speech and body,"

msgctxt "an5.162:5.10"
msgid ""
"yāpissa aparisuddhavacīsamācāratā na sāpissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: tamevassa → tadevassa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.162:5.11"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho so labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, tamevassa "
"tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"and focus on the fact that they get an openness and clarity of heart from "
"time to time."

msgctxt "an5.162:5.12"
msgid "Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (3)"
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro aparisuddhavacīsamācāro na "
"ca labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale "
"āghāto paṭivinetabbo?"
msgstr ""
"How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of "
"body and speech is impure, and who doesn’t get an openness and clarity of "
"heart from time to time?"

msgctxt "an5.162:6.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno "
"addhānamaggappaṭipanno."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was traveling along a road, and they were sick, suffering, "
"gravely ill."

msgctxt "an5.162:6.3"
msgid "Tassa puratopissa dūre gāmo pacchatopissa dūre gāmo."
msgstr "And it was a long way to a village, whether ahead or behind."

# BB has “leader of the village district”, which seems unlikely in the context. gāmantanāyaka is not glossed and doesn’t appear elsewhere. The Chinese text doesn’t, so far as I can tell, have anything closely corresponding to this phrase. Notice also that here, gamanta must mean “village”, not “outskirts of a village”, as usually rendered by BB in AN.
msgctxt "an5.162:6.4"
msgid ""
"So na labheyya sappāyāni bhojanāni, na labheyya sappāyāni bhesajjāni, na "
"labheyya patirūpaṃ upaṭṭhākaṃ, na labheyya gāmantanāyakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And they didn’t have any suitable food or medicine, or a competent carer, or "
"someone to bring them to the neighborhood of a village."

msgctxt "an5.162:6.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aññataro puriso passeyya addhānamaggappaṭipanno."
msgstr "Then another person traveling along the road sees them,"

msgctxt "an5.162:6.6"
msgid ""
"So tasmiṃ purise kāruññaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpeyya, anuddayaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpeyya, "
"anukampaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpeyya:"
msgstr "and thinks of them with nothing but compassion, kindness, and sympathy:"

msgctxt "an5.162:6.7"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāyaṃ puriso labheyya sappāyāni bhojanāni, labheyya sappāyāni "
"bhesajjāni, labheyya patirūpaṃ upaṭṭhākaṃ, labheyya gāmantanāyakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, may this person get suitable food or medicine, or a competent carer, or "
"someone to bring them to the neighborhood of a village."

msgctxt "an5.162:6.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: Māyaṃ → ayaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: āpajjī’ti → āpajjati (bj) | āpajjatīti (pts1) | āpajjeyya (mr)
msgctxt "an5.162:6.9"
msgid "Māyaṃ puriso idheva anayabyasanaṃ āpajjī’ti."
msgstr "So that they don’t come to ruin right here.’"

#. VAR: evarūpepi → evarūpe (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.162:6.10"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro "
"aparisuddhavacīsamācāro na ca labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso "
"pasādaṃ, evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale kāruññaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ anuddayāyeva "
"upaṭṭhāpetabbā anukampāyeva upaṭṭhāpetabbā:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure "
"behavior by way of speech and body, and the fact that they don’t get an "
"openness and clarity of heart from time to time, and think of them with "
"nothing but compassion, kindness, and sympathy:"

msgctxt "an5.162:6.11"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata ayamāyasmā kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveyya, "
"vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveyya, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya "
"manosucaritaṃ bhāveyya."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, may this person give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, "
"and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an5.162:6.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: Māyaṃ āyasmā → māyamāyasmā (s1-3) | ayamāyasmā (mr)
#. VAR: upapajjī’ti → upapajjatīti (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.162:6.13"
msgid ""
"Māyaṃ āyasmā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjī’ti."
msgstr ""
"So that, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re not reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’"

msgctxt "an5.162:6.14"
msgid "Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (4)"
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.190"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo parisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro "
"labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale "
"āghāto paṭivinetabbo?"
msgstr ""
"How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of "
"body and speech is pure, and who gets an openness and clarity of heart from "
"time to time?"

#. VAR: acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā → acchodikā sātodikā sītodikā (bj)
#. VAR: setakā → setodakā (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.162:7.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā supatitthā "
"ramaṇīyā nānārukkhehi sañchannā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with "
"smooth banks, delightful, and shaded by many trees."

msgctxt "an5.162:7.3"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched."

msgctxt "an5.162:7.4"
msgid ""
"So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā nhātvā ca pivitvā ca paccuttaritvā tattheva "
"rukkhacchāyāya nisīdeyya vā nipajjeyya vā."
msgstr ""
"They’d plunge into the lotus pond to bathe and drink. And after emerging "
"they’d sit or lie down right there in the shade of the trees."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:8.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo parisuddhakāyasamācāro "
"parisuddhavacīsamācāro labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso "
"pasādaṃ, yāpissa parisuddhakāyasamācāratā sāpissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi "
"kātabbā;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, at that time you should focus on that person’s pure "
"behavior by way of body and speech, and on the fact that they get an "
"openness and clarity of heart from time to time."

msgctxt "an5.162:8.2"
msgid "yāpissa parisuddhavacīsamācāratā sāpissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.162:8.3"
msgid ""
"yampi labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ "
"samaye manasi kātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.162:8.4"
msgid "Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo."
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person."

msgctxt "an5.162:8.5"
msgid "Samantapāsādikaṃ, āvuso, puggalaṃ āgamma cittaṃ pasīdati. (5)"
msgstr ""
"Relying on a person who is impressive all around, the mind becomes confident."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.162:9.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, āvuso, pañca āghātapaṭivinayā, yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto "
"sabbaso paṭivinetabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of "
"resentment when it has arisen toward anyone.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.162:9.2"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
